Most of the bond lengths, bond angles, and torsion angles fall within the normal ranges indicated by a Mercury Mogul geometry check (Macrae et al., 2008). The $\mathrm{C} 1-\mathrm{C} 2-\mathrm{C} 3$ angle of $114.1^{\circ}$ is flagged as unusual (average $=104.0(32), Z$-score $=$ 3.1). The $\mathrm{Cs}^{+}$cation is 9-coordinate, with a bond-valence sum of $0.92$ valence units. The location of the citrate anion on a mirror plane and the coordination of all seven oxygen atoms to $\mathrm{Cs}^{+}$cations presumably are the source of the slight distortion. The citrate anion occurs in the trans, trans conformation,

